### 2. Backend — Controller
**`server/controllers/pujaBookingController.js`**

Contains 4 exported functions:

#### `getAvailability` — `GET /api/puja-bookings/availability`
Query params: `?pujaId=surya-puja&date=2025-06-15`

Returns:
```json
{
  "date": "2025-06-15",
  "totalSlots": 5,
  "bookedCount": 2,
  "remainingSlots": 3,
  "available": true,
  "bookedTimeWindows": [
    { "start": "07:00", "end": "12:00" },
    { "start": "14:00", "end": "19:00" }
  ]
}
```

The frontend uses `bookedTimeWindows` to warn the user if their chosen time falls inside a locked slot.

#### `createBooking` — `POST /api/puja-bookings`

**Business Rules (enforced server-side):**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rule 1 — Daily Quota:** Max **5 pujas** per `pujaId` per day. If `bookings.length >= 5`, the API returns HTTP `409` with `code: DAILY_LIMIT_REACHED` and the message:
> *"No puja slots available for today. Please choose another date."*

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rule 2 — 5-Hour Time Lock:** When a booking is created at `startTime`, the `endTime` is automatically set to `startTime + 5 hours`. No new booking can overlap this window. If conflict detected, API returns HTTP `409` with `code: TIME_SLOT_CONFLICT` and:
> *"This time slot is locked until HH:MM. Please choose a different time."*

**Lock window example:**
```
Booking A: 08:00 → locked until 13:00
Booking B attempt at 10:00 → ❌ BLOCKED (10:00 is between 08:00 and 13:00)
Booking B attempt at 13:00 → ✅ ALLOWED (no overlap)
```

#### `getAllBookings` — `GET /api/puja-bookings` *(Protected)*
Admin endpoint. Filterable by `?pujaId=&date=&status=`.

#### `updateStatus` — `PATCH /api/puja-bookings/:id/status` *(Protected)*
Admin endpoint. Changes booking status.

